'''Kibi no Takehiko''' (吉備 武彦, きび の たけひこ{{Sfn|Kibi no Takehiko (Ancient Lineages)|2010}}) was a figure from ancient [[Japan]] mentioned in the ''[[Nihon Shoki]]'' and other texts. He is referred to as "Kibi no Takehiko" in the ''Nihon Shoki'' and as "Kibi Takehiko no Mikoto" or "Kibi Tatehiko no Mikoto" in other sources.

He is known as one of the attendants who accompanied {{ill|Yamato Takeru|ja|日本武尊|1=Yamato Takeru|lt=Prince Yamato Takeru|3=ヤマトタケル|12=draft}} during his eastern expedition under the reign of Emperor [[Keikō|Keikō Tennō]]{{Sfn|Kibi no Takehiko (Ancient Lineages)|2010}}.

== Genealogy ==
The ''[[Nihon Shoki]]'' does not provide details on Kibi no Takehiko's origins. However, the ''[[Shinsen Shōjiroku]]'' identifies him as a grandson of {{ill|Wakatakehiko no Mikoto|ja|稚武彦命|12=draft}}, a prince of Emperor [[Kōrei|Kōrei Tennō]]. In some entries, he is listed as a son of Wakatakehiko no Mikoto.

Regarding his descendants, the ''Nihon Shoki'' (Keikō Tennō, Year 51, Eighth Month, Fourth Day entry) records his daughter {{ill|Kibi Anato Takehime|ja|吉備穴戸武媛|12=draft}} as a consort of Yamato Takeru. Together, they had two sons: {{ill|Takekaigo no Mikoto|ja|武卵王|12=draft}} and {{ill|Tōkiwake no Mikoto|ja|十城別王|12=draft}}. Additionally, the ''Nihon Shoki'' (Ōjin Tennō, Year 22, Ninth Month, Tenth Day entry) and the ''[[Nihon Sandai Jitsuroku]]'' (Engi 3, 879 CE) list other children, including {{ill|Urakogori Waketakehiko|ja|浦凝別|12=draft}} (founder of the Enō clan), {{ill|Mitomo Waketakehiko|ja|御友別|12=draft}} (founder of the Kibi clan), {{ill|Kamo Waketakehiko|ja|鴨別|12=draft}} (founder of the Kasa clan), and {{ill|Anehime|ja|兄媛|12=draft}} (consort of Ōjin Tennō).
