He is known as one of the attendants who accompanied {{ill|Yamato Takeru|ja|日本武尊|1=Yamato Takeru|lt=Prince Yamato Takeru|3=ヤマトタケル|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yamato Takeru|13=User:Immanuelle/Yamato Takeru|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to ヤマトタケル|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q461258}} during his eastern expedition under the reign of Emperor [[Keikō|Keikō Tennō]]{{Sfn|Kibi no Takehiko (Ancient Lineages)|2010}}.

== Genealogy ==
The ''[[Nihon Shoki]]'' does not provide details on Kibi no Takehiko's origins. However, the ''{{ill|Shinsen Shōjiroku|en|Shinsen Shōjiroku|qid=Q1045362|lt=Shinsen Shōjiroku|1=Shinsen Shōjiroku}}'' identifies him as a grandson of {{ill|Wakatakehiko no Mikoto|ja|稚武彦命|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Wakatakehiko no Mikoto|1=Wakatakehiko|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q11596350}}, a prince of Emperor [[Kōrei|Kōrei Tennō]]. In some entries, he is listed as a son of Wakatakehiko no Mikoto.

Regarding his descendants, the ''Nihon Shoki'' (Keikō Tennō, Year 51, Eighth Month, Fourth Day entry) records his daughter {{ill|Kibi Anato Takehime|ja|吉備穴戸武媛|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kibi Anato Takehime|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} as a consort of Yamato Takeru. Together, they had two sons: {{ill|Takekaigo no Mikoto|ja|武卵王|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Takekaigo no Mikoto|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} and {{ill|Tōkiwake no Mikoto|ja|十城別王|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tōkiwake no Mikoto|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}. Additionally, the ''Nihon Shoki'' (Ōjin Tennō, Year 22, Ninth Month, Tenth Day entry) and the ''[[Nihon Sandai Jitsuroku]]'' (Engi 3, 879 CE) list other children, including {{ill|Urakogori Waketakehiko|ja|浦凝別|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Urakogori Waketakehiko|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} (founder of the Enō clan), {{ill|Mitomo Waketakehiko|ja|御友別|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Mitomo Waketakehiko|1=Miyotowake|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q18235575}} (founder of the Kibi clan), {{ill|Kamo Waketakehiko|ja|鴨別|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kamo Waketakehiko|1=Q18226142|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q18226142}} (founder of the Kasa clan), and {{ill|Anehime|ja|兄媛|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Anehime|1=Ehime|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q119380627}} (consort of Ōjin Tennō).
